column23: Flock of CONI observed foraging over the Sandy River.  High count of 17 CONI observed at one time.  CONI were observed throughout the survey, but often fewer than 17 were seen at any given time.  Fifteen of them were entered on one line on the survey sheet, but each was entered individually on the spreadsheet.  Since it was impossible to keep track of individuals, the entire group was entered as having been observed throughout the entire surevey.
Light fog at ground level.  Water rushing through culvert.
First AMRO detected was very close and very loud.
Coyotes started singing during the final minute of the survey.
